In the guidelines, the dot touches the 冖.

In commercial fonts, the dot never touches in the Sung typeface, and may touch or join
depending on the available space for the Hei typeface.

It should never touch in the Sung typeface, and touch or join in the Hei typeface
depending on design requirements.

When 穴 is used on the top, the last stroke is changed to a bent stroke, e.g. 空.

Some commercial fonts also use a hook, i.e. use 儿.

Use a bent stroke or bent stroke with hook when 穴 is used on top.
